body:
**Description**

Facing error while using SkiaSharp library in OpenShift container

**Code**

```
        SKBitmap bitmap = new SKBitmap(100, 100, SKImageInfo.PlatformColorType, SKAlphaType.Premul);
        var surface = SKSurface.Create(bitmap.Info);
        SKCanvas canvas = surface.Canvas;
        canvas.Clear(SKColors.White);
        var paint = new SKPaint();
        paint.IsAntialias = true;
        paint.Color = SKColors.Red;
        paint.StrokeWidth = 3;
        string fontName = SKTypeface.Default.FamilyName;
        canvas.DrawCircle(50, 50, 25, paint);
        var image = SKImage.FromBitmap(bitmap);
        var data = surface.Snapshot().Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Jpeg, 80);
        MemoryStream outputStream = new MemoryStream();
        data.SaveTo(outputStream);
        outputStream.Position = 0;
```

**Expected Behavior**

Should draw the circle as expected.

**Actual Behavior**

Below exception thrown from line no. 1.
`The type initializer for 'SkiaSharp.SKImageInfo' threw an exception.`

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  SkiaSharp 2.80.2
- IDE:  Microsoft Visual Studio Professional 2019, Version 16.8.4
- Platform Target Frameworks: ASP.NET Core 3.1 targeted application in Red Hat OpenShift container

**Note:** Already we have tried to resolve this issue by installing **SkiaSharpNativeAssets.Linux**, **SkiaSharpNativeAssets.NoDependencies** packages. But nothing helps.


**Reproduction Link**

Kindly deploy the below sample in Red Hat OpenShift container to replicate this issue,
https://github.com/RamarajMarimuthu/s2i-dotnetcore-ex/tree/SkApp

**References**
https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/4.3/applications/application_life_cycle_management/odc-creating-applications-using-developer-perspective.html
https://www.openshift.com/blog/how-to-deploy-an-application-from-git-to-openshift
